    .lang.lang-en
      h1 Potcoava Lake (652 ha)
      p
        | This strictly protected area is located within the river delta, to the North of Gorgova-Isac lacustrian complex and includes Babinţii Mari, Babinţii Mici and Potcoava lakes. Inside the lakes there have been identified 41 algae species, typical for eutro-hipertrophic lakes, 48 superior plants species, among which Water Chestnut and Iris. Among the invertebrates, there are 31 plankton species and 6 benthonic. The fish population includes 20 species, among which the Tench and Crucian Carp are found in large numbers. There are 4 mammal species, 2 reptile species and about 100 bird species. The lake is also a nesting place for water species (ducks, coots, Water Rails, grebes, etc), including mixed colonies of herons, Glossy Ibis, Little Egret and Pigmy Cormorant. 
      p
        | The habitat types are: dystrophic lakes and ponds (code 3160); oligotrophic stagnant waters, up to mezotrophic with 
        em Littorelletea uniflorae 
        |and/or 
        em Isoëto-Nanojuncetea 
        |vegetation (code 3130); natural eutrophic lakes with 
        em Magnopotamion 
        |or 
        em Hydrocharition 
        |vegetation (code 3150); river meadows with 
        em Salix alba 
        |and 
        em Populus alba 
        |(code 92A0). 
